  "prerequisites": [],
  "keyPoints": [
    "Choose the right database type for the job: SQL for relational data, document stores for flexible schemas, Redis for caching and real-time features",
    "Good schema design with normalization, indexes, and proper relationships prevents expensive refactors later",
    "ORMs like Prisma abstract SQL away but understanding raw SQL remains essential for debugging and optimization",
    "REST, GraphQL, and tRPC each solve different API design problems -- pick the one that fits your team and project",
    "Validate data at every layer: client, API, and database to prevent bad data from ever being stored",
    "Caching at multiple levels (CDN, HTTP headers, Redis, in-memory) is the single biggest performance lever",
    "Schema migrations let you evolve your database safely with version-controlled, reversible changes",
    "Real-time data with WebSockets and SSE enables live dashboards, chat, and collaborative editing",
    "Security is not optional: parameterized queries, encryption, and access control protect your users and your business"
  ],
